In Shenzhen in early February, the flowers in the park are already in full bloom. Unlike in previous years, the streets have been quiet and empty with the new coronavirus outbreak. But according to Tao Canming, today's correspondent, despite the severity of the outbreak, people in the city are still taking advantage of limited opportunities to pass on warmth to one another.

Everything, including flowers and bread, is on the side of life

By Tao canming

The only two valid reasons for going out now are to visit my father in the neighborhood next door and to be on duty at the school.

Visiting my father, from home to home, to send some supplies to talk about the current epidemic, is the greatest joy of family life. Now the biggest fear is that he lives in this building patients, according to the rules just issued, the whole building will be sealed off, he can not get out, we can not enter, if that, to the 80-year-old father who insisted on living alone, is a great test.

Fifteen Shangyuan festival, is a trip in my mind can not go, at dusk to buy a pig bones and carrots to wash him cut good stew, father said, not stew at Night; want to give him a few dumplings, he said to come.

So, just talking. Not Close enough. We came in from the outside.

To the school on duty, since the people of the whole country sat at home to "suffocate" the virus, drive to the school on duty like a yard. The last day I was on duty was just the beginning of spring. There was a heavy rain in the morning. The air was as fresh as water. The thin water on the newly-built green playground reflected the whole teaching building. It was a beautiful sight I had never seen before.

Came to school today on a mission.

February 9 is the last day before the start of work, people back to the deep work, probably one after another to come back, although the school dormitory is not to face the students until the end of February teachers, but the rules are the same. We're GONNA set up a separate corridor for them outside the school district.

Watching the two security guards work our route, I said I'd go out and look around, as if I were in charge.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The streets of Shenzhen under epidemic situation

So out of the gate, I walked along the Empty Street to the mini park to the west of the school. I wanted to walk through the park and farther, not knowing where I was going.

Besides, walking down the street, you feel guilty.

PIZANIK'S LINE COMES TO MIND:

Here's the hard part:

Walking down the street

Point to the sky or the earth

Several trees in the Park Pink Bauhinia flowers in full bloom, and the garden of Hibiscus is bright. I do not want to say that the flowers are blooming lonely, they open their own flowers, this is not for us to see.

There were only three old people wearing masks in the whole small park. During the epidemic prevention campaign, I found that the old people could not sit still any longer than the young people. These aunts, who are accustomed to walking around and dancing in the square, in more than 10 hours of flights are common to them to walk around the cabin to practice a few moves, now day after day squatting at home, estimated to be really painful.

An aunt was walking along the wall of the building inside the park, as if she realized something was wrong with her running out. I wanted to shout at her, "Auntie, since you are out, you should walk around the empty place in a noisy way, and then go home as soon as possible. " Another old couple went to the side of the road with swords on their backs, a professional trainer in a heavy coat, and, uh, I think I just got the full set.

Soon came to Jingtian North Street and Xiangmei Road intersection, the usual busy intersection, now quiet, nearby Xiangmei north station subway entrance only heard the sound of the elevator idling, no one was transmitted up. I even pressed the Stopwatch to see how long it would take for a human being to emerge from the elevator. A minute later, I was bored.

Across the traffic lights came and bought food bags of people, each other bowed their heads.

I remembered that in the neighborhood not far from Qiaoxiang road, my good friend of more than 10 years lived there. In the past, I had a coffee appointment from time to time. During the Spring Festival, I had a family reunion. In a blink of an eye, I hadn't seen her for a long time, i had the impulse to call her to meet me at the intersection for a chat.

The sight of a queue of cars on the side of the road was a miracle after the outbreak. Originally, the front is the supermarket, each vehicle must check the body temperature, even if the vehicle is not much, also like the turtle line.

Roadside drunk butterflies and a bunch of red flowers into the sea, but also dotted with some swaying mango grass, as if ambitious to create an urban wilderness. Well, now the roads in Shenzhen are really spacious enough to graze cattle.

It seems that many people are using the weekend to come to the mall to replenish "feed" , there is still a long two weeks to endure, I do not know after the epidemic, there will be "boil spring" such a word out, and "cat winter" corresponding.

It suddenly occurred to me that all the way down to the South side of the supermarket were flower stalls. Now that I was here, I should buy some flowers. The roses and lilies and daffodils that had been in the house years before had fallen off the line, and needed a fresh fragrance to dispel the disinfecting water that was always in the room.

Disappointingly, the flower shops in the center of the street have all been evacuated. In a small corner outside the supermarket, there is a small surviving flower stall. A small boss is sorting out a few pails of fresh flowers, yellow Rose, red rose, lily and a few other flowers.

Lilies are $15 a pop.

I know. 12 bucks buys you a great one.

The boss pulled out a lily, "I sell this are 20 one, now want to sell out quickly closed file, you see it. "

Sure enough, not the usual four-headed five, each branch has eight or nine heads.

"Wrap three sticks. " I calculate roughly three sticks have almost 25, is enough.

Instead of holding a newspaper or a piece of clear plastic paper, the boss deliberately found a dark green ribbon-like wrapping paper, so that a bunch of the most ordinary red lily suddenly have a higher taste.

The boss is a talker. He was originally from Xiangxi, Jishou. He didn't go home for the New Year. Luckily, he didn't.

I told him we were from the same town.

He said very well that Changsha is now better developed in Yuelu District and Furong District.

"after selling these flowers, we need to rest for a while. Now the epidemic is so severe, let's just get through this period first, " the boss wrapped very carefully. "To be honest, I'm a little scared. "

"Well, first take care of yourself and protect yourself, " I nodded.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Looking up at his mask so thin, like a layer of fragile paper about to burst, nose clip place by his repeated lifting has changed color, I do not know this mask he reluctantly wear for how long, the market must be required to wear a mask, but, you can't buy a mask anywhere. Where can you get a mask like that.

I wish I had an extra mask on me today. I feel a little sorry for you.

I looked down at the barrels of flowers, very worried, "sell out today? "

"It's not much, there aren't many flower shops open now, they'll be sold out soon, " he said confidently.

"Well, " I said cheerfully, taking the heavy bunch of lilies, "have a good day and a good day. Good luck with your business. "

"Wait, wait, give you a few forget-me-not. " The boss turned to the big bucket of Purple Pink forget-me-not handed over.

"No, no, no, " I said.

"They're the freshest, not the ones that have been sitting there for a long time. Take them and be my guest. "

Solemnly accepted the New Year gift, solemnly said: "thank you. "

On the way back, I saw the community police posted in front of a store and a fast-food restaurant. Thinking about the busy security guards at the school, I decided to pack some Chinese food for them to go home and set foot in the empty restaurant, "No, no, no, don't come in. If you come in, we'll have to close up shop. "

Oh, oh, I remember just seeing on the door of a shop that had not yet opened, a clause in the notice for the reopening of its business, that "no snack bar or restaurant shall be allowed to eat in the house, and shall be packed up for the public to take away" , and you're GONNA do it right in front of the store. One operation is not legal, implicating the staff to take their own mobile phone to try to run to the front desk for me to order all kinds of busy, almost sweating.

I finally ordered, and I just stood in front of the door.

A tall man, also blocked by the door, rushed forward.

He began to call, his tone full of impatience, "So controlled that you can't even get into the store, what do you want to eat? Well, now you don't even have to eat. What do you want? "

"Oh, Darling, be good, daddy will come home. " A baby whines to daddy in the telephone.

I just listen to this strong man in my side to the telephone end of the mother and son will talk in the tone of "Hao Heng" and "Sweet Greasy" between seamless switching, is very interesting. I suppressed a laugh and watched as the big man took two chicken rolls and left.

When I went back to the bakery on the corner to buy some bread, I found that they had tactfully barred the customers from the front door, leaving freshly baked bread in the high bakery counter.

I couldn't see straight, little sister. I craned my neck. "I'll have the whole wheat, no seven and eight, and a, uh, plain bread. "

My little sister turned the two bread racks around and picked out two whole-wheat, cone-shaped Raisin Buns for me.

Hand it over and put it in your hand. It's still warm. Just a little bit warm, fall in the palm of the hand, only feel the world is beautiful.

"thank you. You take care. "

I held the bouquet, carrying food, back to the Cold Street, to the familiar campus.

Live well, for all things, including flowers and bread, are on the side of life, not on the side of death.
